### =============================================================
### Imperium News API — Endpoint Tests
### Base URL: http://localhost:8999
### Topics from imperium_topic_taxonomy:
###   politics_government | war_security | crime_justice
###   business_economy | science_technology | health
###   sports | entertainment_culture | lifestyle_travel
###   education | environment_weather | disasters_accidents
###   religion_society
### =============================================================

@baseUrl = http://localhost:8999/api/v1

### ——————————————————————————————————————————————
### TOPICS — Onboarding picker
### ——————————————————————————————————————————————

### 0a. Get all active topics (cache-aside: Redis → Postgres)
### Expected: [{ "topicId": "politics_government", "displayName": "Politics & Government" }, ...]
GET {{baseUrl}}/topics
Accept: application/json

###

### ——————————————————————————————————————————————
### STAGE 1: USER ONBOARDING
### ——————————————————————————————————————————————

### 1a. Onboard — single topic (Science & Technology)
POST {{baseUrl}}/users/onboard
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "topics": [ "science_technology" , "health" , "war_security" ],
  "countryId": 1
}

###

### 1b. Onboard — multiple topics (Politics + Business)
POST {{baseUrl}}/users/onboard
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "topics": ["politics_government", "business_economy"],
  "countryId": 1
}

###

### 1c. Onboard — Health + Sports user
POST {{baseUrl}}/users/onboard
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "topics": ["health", "sports"],
  "countryId": 2
}

###

### 1d. Onboard — all major topics
POST {{baseUrl}}/users/onboard
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "topics": [
    "politics_government",
    "war_security",
    "crime_justice",
    "business_economy",
    "science_technology",
    "health",
    "sports",
    "entertainment_culture",
    "lifestyle_travel",
    "education",
    "environment_weather",
    "disasters_accidents",
    "religion_society"
  ],
  "countryId": 1
}

###

### ——————————————————————————————————————————————
### STAGE 2: FEED ENGINE
### ——————————————————————————————————————————————
### NOTE: Replace {{userId}} with the UUID returned from onboarding above.

@userId = 33598717-e778-4ffc-bfbf-22312bd526fb

### 2a. Get initial feed — default limit (20)
GET {{baseUrl}}/feed?userId={{userId}}
Accept: application/json

###

### 2b. Get initial feed — custom limit of 5
GET {{baseUrl}}/feed?userId={{userId}}&limit=10
Accept: application/json

###

### 2c. Get next page — cursor scrolling
### Replace cursor value with the `nextCursor` from the previous response
@cursor = 1777315086

GET {{baseUrl}}/feed?userId={{userId}}&limit=10&cursor={{cursor}}
Accept: application/json

###

### 2d. Get next page — second scroll
### Replace cursor with the `nextCursor` from the previous page 2 response
@cursor2 = 1777314725274

GET {{baseUrl}}/feed?userId={{userId}}&limit=5&cursor={{cursor2}}
Accept: application/json

###

### ——————————————————————————————————————————————
### STAGE 2: VIEW TRACKING
### ——————————————————————————————————————————————

### 3a. Mark articles as viewed — single article
POST {{baseUrl}}/feed/views
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "REPLACE_WITH_UUID_FROM_ONBOARDING",
  "articleIds": ["REPLACE_WITH_ARTICLE_ID_FROM_FEED"]
}

###

### 3b. Mark articles as viewed — multiple articles (batch)
POST {{baseUrl}}/feed/views
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "userId": "REPLACE_WITH_UUID_FROM_ONBOARDING",
  "articleIds": [
    "REPLACE_WITH_ARTICLE_ID_1",
    "REPLACE_WITH_ARTICLE_ID_2",
    "REPLACE_WITH_ARTICLE_ID_3"
  ]
}

###

### 3c. Get feed again — viewed articles should NOT appear
GET {{baseUrl}}/feed?userId={{userId}}&limit=5
Accept: application/json

###
### ——————————————————————————————————————————————
### STAGE 3: ARTICLE DOMAIN & BOOKMARKS
### ——————————————————————————————————————————————
### NOTE: Replace {{articleId}} with a real ID from the feed response.

@articleId = 565300956

### 4a. Fetch Full Article Details (Cache-aside)
GET {{baseUrl}}/articles/{{articleId}}
Accept: application/json

###

### 4b. Bookmark an Article
POST {{baseUrl}}/users/{{userId}}/bookmarks/{{articleId}}
Accept: application/json

###

### 4c. Fetch User's Saved Articles (Bookmarks)
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/{{userId}}/bookmarks
Accept: application/json

###

### 4d. Remove a Bookmark
DELETE {{baseUrl}}/users/{{userId}}/bookmarks/{{articleId}}
Accept: application/json

###

### 4e. Verify Bookmarks after removal
GET {{baseUrl}}/users/{{userId}}/bookmarks
Accept: application/json
